description: Plush beds, on-site dining and the cable cars three blocks away thrill Priceline guests at the non-smoking InterContinental San Francisco, which also has a hot tub.  Towering 32 stories over SoMa near Union Square, the hotel's arctic-blue exterior is a distinctive city landmark. The 550 non-smoking, spacious, light-filled rooms boast floor-to-ceiling windows, with particularly dramatic city views from the upper floors. Accommodations include 42-inch HDTVs, iPod docks, coffeemakers, Wi-Fi (fee), and plush beds with Serta Perfect Sleeper mattresses. Sip a vintage grappa from the bar, or take a meal in the Michelin-starred California-Italian restaurant. The hotel also has a spa, fitness room, hot tub and outdoor terrace.  The InterContinental is in SoMa next to Moscone Center, three blocks southeast of the Powell Street BART station and cable cars. Take a stroll two blocks east to Yerba Buena Gardens. If you're driving from the airports, the hotel is 14 miles north of San Francisco International Airport and 20 miles northwest of Oakland International Airport.   "Loved the location" say Priceline guests of this "very elegant" InterContinental with cushy beds and "amazing views."

location.neighborhoodDescription: Convention-goers and culture lovers flock to this area south of Market Street, home to the largest convention hall in the city and a heady concentration of museums. There's something for everyone at the San Francisco Museum of Modern Art, Museum of the African Diaspora, the Contemporary Jewish Museum, Children's Creativity Museum and the Cartoon Museum. Yerba Buena Gardens provide refreshing green open space. Streetcar lines above and below Market Street make exploring a snap.
